<div class="expanded">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Hide information" title="Hide information">Our Business</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Institutional Mortgage Services (IMS) is an industry leader in the business of financing and purchasing mortgage loans. Institutional Mortgage Services (IMS) is comprised of two distinct teams: Correspondent Lending and Warehouse Lending within the Sales  &amp; Fulfillment organization. Both channels are committed to responsible lending and helping create successful home ownership by offering specialized products and services designed to meet the needs of mortgage providers throughout the country - including banks, savings and loans, credit unions, mortgage lenders and mortgage brokers. IMS combines both channels into one business-to-business mortgage team that consistently generates at least 50 percent of the overall volume for the sales and fulfillment channels of Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Home Loans.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">The Institutional Mortgage Services (IMS) Development Program (IDP) is a cutting edge program designed to develop future leaders for the IMS line of business within Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Home Loans. The program prepares select individuals with an opportunity to jump start their careers through an intense training curriculum that provides a breadth of knowledge that would typically several years to develop.</p>
<p class="bac">IDP candidates participate in a balanced learning approach that includes both classroom and on the job training, with ongoing coaching and mentoring opportunities provided every step of the way.</p>
<p class="bac">IDP associates receive ongoing coaching and feedback and participate in a number of exposure events, allowing participants to network and interact with members of the IMS leadership team. It&#39;s an unparalleled career opportunity that gives associates the best possible start in their career.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Qualifications</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Bachelor&#39;s degree</li>
	<li>GPA of 3.0 or higher</li>
	<li>Excellent organizational, analytical, and communications skills</li>
	<li>Strong interpersonal skills and financial aptitude</li>
	<li>Time Management and Problem Solving skills</li>
	<li>Flexible approach to a fast-changing work environment</li>
	<li>Ability to relocate as necessary</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information">Training</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">The 2 year curriculum is designed to develop and enhance a wide variety of highly sought-after skills. The first month of training focuses on building a core foundational knowledge of the mortgage banking industry, as well as an overview of the leadership and soft skills needed for success in the workplace.</p>
<p class="bac">Following the first month of training, candidates will rotate through the core lines of business within IMS including but not limited to: Fulfillment, Credit Strategies, Loss Mitigation, Products  &amp; Pricing, Warehouse Lending  &amp; Counterparty Risk and Sales, providing a deep dive into the organization. Practical learning opportunities abound, allowing associates to fully comprehend each business unit and how it contributes to the organization as a whole.</p>
</div></div>

